# rocm-exporter.service — Host-first deployment systemd unit

## Overview

This systemd unit file runs AMD's official rocm-exporter to expose GPU VRAM
and ROCm metrics for the LLM proxy stack monitoring infrastructure. It uses
the host-first model (binary installation, no containers) and is designed to
be deployed as a **user service** (recommended), though a system-service
variant is documented below.

The rocm-exporter provides Prometheus-compatible metrics including:
- `rocm_vram_total_bytes` — Total VRAM per GPU
- `rocm_vram_used_bytes` — Used VRAM per GPU
- `rocm_vram_free_bytes` — Free VRAM per GPU

Metrics are scraped by Prometheus and visualized in the Grafana dashboard.

## User Service (Recommended)

**File location**: `~/.config/systemd/user/rocm-exporter.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=AMD ROCm exporter for GPU VRAM metrics
After=network.target
Wants=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
ExecStart=/home/rgardler/bin/rocm-exporter/rocm-exporter --web.listen-address=:5000

# Restart policy
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

# Logging
StandardOutput=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/rocm-exporter/logs/rocm-exporter.log
StandardError=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/rocm-exporter/logs/rocm-exporter.log

# Resource limits
MemoryMax=512M

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

### Setup commands (user service)

```bash
# 1. Download and install the rocm-exporter binary
ROCM_EXPORTER_VERSION="0.1.0"  # Check https://github.com/amd/rocm-exporter/releases for latest
wget "https://github.com/amd/rocm-exporter/releases/download/v${ROCM_EXPORTER_VERSION}/rocm-exporter-${ROCM_EXPORTER_VERSION}.linux-amd64.tar.gz"
tar xzf rocm-exporter-${ROCM_EXPORTER_VERSION}.linux-amd64.tar.gz
mkdir -p ~/bin/rocm-exporter
cp rocm-exporter ~/bin/rocm-exporter/
rm -rf rocm-exporter rocm-exporter-${ROCM_EXPORTER_VERSION}.linux-amd64.tar.gz

# 2. Create log directory
mkdir -p ~/.local/state/rocm-exporter/logs

# 3. Install and start the service
cp docs/systemd/rocm-exporter.service ~/.config/systemd/user/rocm-exporter.service
systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user enable rocm-exporter.service
systemctl --user start rocm-exporter.service

# 4. Verify
systemctl --user status rocm-exporter.service
journalctl --user -u rocm-exporter.service -f
```

## System Service (Alternative)

Use this approach only if the rocm-exporter must survive logout or run
independently of any user session. This requires root or sudo access.

**File location**: `/etc/systemd/system/rocm-exporter.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=AMD ROCm exporter for GPU VRAM metrics
After=network.target
Wants=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=rgardler
Group=rgardler
ExecStart=/home/rgardler/bin/rocm-exporter/rocm-exporter --web.listen-address=:5000

Restart=always
RestartSec=5

StandardOutput=append:/var/log/rocm-exporter/rocm-exporter.log
StandardError=append:/var/log/rocm-exporter/rocm-exporter.log

MemoryMax=512M

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

### Setup commands (system service)

```bash
# Create log directory
sudo mkdir -p /var/log/rocm-exporter
sudo chown rgardler:rgardler /var/log/rocm-exporter

# Install the unit
sudo cp docs/systemd/rocm-exporter.service /etc/systemd/system/
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable rocm-exporter.service
sudo systemctl start rocm-exporter.service

# Check status
sudo systemctl status rocm-exporter.service

# View logs
sudo journalctl -u rocm-exporter.service -f
```

## Pre-installation checks

Before installing the rocm-exporter, verify ROCm is properly installed and
GPU is accessible:

```bash
# Check ROCm version
rocm-smi --showtag

# Check GPU status
rocm-smi --showmeminfo vram

# Expected output should show VRAM total and used values for at least one GPU
```

## Verification

Regardless of deployment approach, verify the exporter is running and
exposing metrics:

```bash
# Check metrics endpoint
curl http://localhost:5000/metrics | grep rocm_vram

# Expected metrics (example values):
#   rocm_vram_total_bytes{gpu_id="0"} 17179869184  # 16 GB
#   rocm_vram_used_bytes{gpu_id="0"}  8589934592   # 8 GB
#   rocm_vram_free_bytes{gpu_id="0"} 8589934592    # 8 GB

# Check specific VRAM metrics
curl http://localhost:5000/metrics | grep -E "rocm_vram_(total|used|free)_bytes"
```

## Prometheus scrape configuration

Add the following scrape job to Prometheus configuration:

```yaml
scrape_configs:
  - job_name: "rocm-exporter"
    static_configs:
      - targets: ["localhost:5000"]
    metrics_path: /metrics
```

This is already configured in `monitoring/prometheus.yml`.

## Log paths

- **User service**: `~/.local/state/rocm-exporter/logs/rocm-exporter.log`
- **System service**: `/var/log/rocm-exporter/rocm-exporter.log`

